{
  "stem": "9168.6",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I became, pretty much, a, a career military officer wife, with all of the attendant duties, which was not a happy thing for me.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, that was not my, you know, the-- my plans for life to hold, have coffees for officers' wives at military bases.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I soon learned how to get out of that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then he was assigned to Hart, Michigan, for a new artillery base opening there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was 1949, I think.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we lived on the lake.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a marvelous duty, if you will, for military, and then back on his military duty in Detroit for a period of time.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I did not work in the court system again for several years. 1951, I think it was, well, he was assigned to Fort Leonard Wood in Missouri.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was there that the Judge Advocate General learned that there was a live court reporter had moved into the Fort Leonard Wood area and contacted me.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I worked courts-martial with a very nice arrangement with them, where I could do all the transcript at home-- the murder trials in the courts-martial, Fort Leonard Wood.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And about 1952, we went to Fort Riley, Kansas on his military duty, from where he went to Korea and was a front line officer over there.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I went back to Detroit, to my mother's dur-- for this period of time while he was in Korea.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And at that time, our younger son was born, Peter Alan, who is now in petroleum engineer down in Houston.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My older son is here in Denver, John Kimberly.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
